The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, April 2: The government has decided to accord mi- nority status to Jains. 

 With a little over 55,000 members, the community makes up 0.07 per cent of Bengals population.

 Singur: Three guards returning home on Sunday night after duty at the Tata Motors project site here were attacked by miscreants. Police said the guards, who patrol the fencing around the site, were hit with rods. They were rushed to the Singur rural hospital. The Trinamul Congress-led Krishi Jomi Raksha Committee denied having any hand in the incident. CPM district committee member Dibakar Das said the guards had given up their land for the project.

 Krishnagar: A 17-year-old girl committed suicide on Sunday after she was beaten up by villagers who accused her of having an affair with the 12-year son of a neighbour. Police said Jharna Sardar had been spotted holding the boys hands in the village.




